  "texts": [
    "Specifically, our contributions are summarized as follows:• We present SNCS, a novel community search approach that utilizes topic models to account for content preferences, which has not been explored before (Sect. 4).",
    "• Our study is the first to utilize meta-structures to improve the quality of community search in heterogeneous graphs.",
    "Additionally, we develop an efficient graph reconstruction algorithm to tackle the high time complexity associated with searching through meta-structures.",
    "The algorithm is based on cutting-edge community search techniques and is proved to be effective in our analysis (Sect. 4).",
    "• We conduct comprehensive experiments on real HGs to demonstrate the efficiency and effectiveness of our proposed SNCS approach."
  ],
